- Not all imported goods have duties; some may be exempt.
- Duties may apply to the importer, not directly to the goods.
- Duties might be required by law but not necessarily imposed on every imported item.
- Certain goods might fall under free trade agreements, exempting them from duties.
- Duties could be waived under specific circumstances or for certain importers.
- The context specifies the importer pays duties, not that all goods inherently have them.